lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2731  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors express HRP-fused recombinant NLGN2A and observe stainging of the synaptic cleft. NLGN2A is a postsynaptic TM adhesion protein that is known to be able to induce presynaptic differentiation of GABAergic synapses. The postsynaptic localization is not resolved in these figures (difficult for epitopes/proteins in/around the synaptic cleft) but known from other literature (seen f.i. ticket #2755 that shows expression in the postsynapse). This aspect is implicitly acknowledged by the authors since the study uses HPR-tagging of postsynaptic proteins to separate Glut from GABA synapses (Fig.1A). Experimental description: - \"Dissociated Rat Neuron Culture\"\n- The species of the overexpressed proteins is not stated. The authors were contacted for additional information (dd. 23/2/2018, ayting@stanford.edu). Author replied:\n\n\"the genes are:\nSLITRK3 human\nLRRTM1: human\nLRRTM2: human\nNLGN2A: rat\n\nbest wishes,\n\nKen Loh\nPostdoctoral Associate\nFriedman Lab\n(formerly Ting lab)\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2731" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

